Students are advised to take at least one upper-division course focusing on modeling and simulation to solve biological problems.
Students can obtain course credit for research by enrolling in BIOL195 and for major research projects by enrolling in BIOL198.
Minor degrees in biology and related disciplines (biotechnology, biomedical engineering, public health, and environmental studies) are available.
Students seeking a secondary school teaching credential in biology must pass the California Subject Examination for Teachers (CSET) and consult with the department coordinator.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/biology.html#3aca1358926e'),
('Anthropology', 'The anthropology major combines foundational courses, statistical and methodological training, upper-division electives across subfields, and speaker series participation.', 'ANTH', 0, '(ANTH1 & ANTH2 & ANTH3 & (ANTH4 | ANTH5 | ANTH6 | ANTH7 | ANTH12A) & (ANTH50 | ENVS50) & ANTH110 & (MATH8 | BIO160 | ENVS110 | PSYC105 | POLI101) & (ANTH111 | ANTH112 | ANTH113) & (ENVS116 | ENVS116A | ETHN165 | PHSC50 | PSYC105 | BIO160 | ENVS110 | WGST102 | ANTH111 | ANTH112 | ANTH113) & ANTH114 & ANTH198 & 6(ANTH130-139 | ANTH140-149 | ANTH173 | ANTH186 | ANTH189 | ANTH150-179 | ANTH184 | ANTH185 | ANTH187 | ANTH188))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Anthropology Speaker Series events","requirementDescription":"Attend six Anthropology Speaker Series events"},{"requirementName":"Upper-division category representation","requirementDescription":"Six upper-division courses must include at least one course from each of archaeology, biological anthropology, and cultural anthropology"}]', 'Honors thesis option available', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/anthropology.html#f7bf97d9b9e0'),
('Art History', 'Art History majors examine visual and material culture across space and time, develop critical thinking, research, and writing skills, and prepare for careers or graduate study in art history and related fields.', 'ARTH', 0, '4(ARTH1-99) & 5(ARTH100-199) & 2(ARTS1-199) & 2(ARTH1-99 | ARTH100-199) & ARTH100 & ARTH196', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Upper-division advanced writing requirement","requirementDescription":"One of the five upper-division ARTH courses must be an ARTH upper-division advanced writing course."},{"requirementName":"Limit on ARTH 98/198 and 194 credit","requirementDescription":"Only 4 units of ARTH 98/198 or ARTH 194 may count toward the art history major."},{"requirementName":"Study abroad and transfer credit restrictions","requirementDescription":"No more than three study abroad courses may be accepted; only one upper-division study abroad course may fulfill the upper-division ARTH requirement; only approved study abroad courses per the equivalency database may be accepted as transfer credit."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/art-and-art-history.html#f7994386b4fd'),
('Studio Art', 'Studio Art majors develop conceptual and technical competence, engage in critical analysis, and produce a senior body of original artwork exhibited with an artist’s statement, preparing for further study or careers in fine or commercial arts.', 'ARTS', 0, '13(ARTS1-199) & 4(ARTH1-199)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Foundation course requirements","requirementDescription":"ARTS 30, ARTS 74, one two-dimensional foundation course (ARTS 32 or ARTS 72), and one three-dimensional foundation course (ARTS 33, ARTS 63, or ARTS 64)."},{"requirementName":"Additional studio electives","requirementDescription":"Six additional ARTS elective courses (excluding ARTS 194 and ARTS 198), at least three of which must be upper-division."},{"requirementName":"Required studio courses","requirementDescription":"ARTS 100 (junior year), ARTS 190 (fall of senior year), and ARTS 196 (winter and spring of senior year)."},{"requirementName":"Art History course requirements","requirementDescription":"Four ARTH courses: one lower-division ARTH (excluding ARTH 11A), one ARTH global course, one ARTH upper-division modern or contemporary course, and one ARTH upper-division advanced writing course."},{"requirementName":"Study abroad and transfer credit restrictions","requirementDescription":"No more than half of the requirements may be accepted as study abroad courses; only one art history study abroad course may count; only approved courses per the equivalency database may be accepted as transfer credit."},{"requirementName":"Emphasis limitation","requirementDescription":"Studio Art majors may complete only one emphasis."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/art-and-art-history.html#f7994386b4fd'),
('Child Studies', 'Designed for undergraduates interested in careers working with children and families in school or community settings, with a curriculum emphasizing social justice, anti-racist perspective, and cultural competence. Students engage extensively with local schools and community-based programs to address issues affecting marginalized populations. Graduates earn a Bachelor of Science and are prepared for advanced study and professional careers in education, social services, counseling, law, therapy, and nonprofit work.', 'CHST', 0, '(CHST3 & CHST4 & CHST5 & CHST6 & CHST11 & CHST12 & CHST75 & CHST100 & CHST101 & CHST102 & CHST104 & CHST106 & CHST180 & CHST181 & CHST182) & (PSYC2 & PSYC185) & 1(CHST66 | CHST109 | CHST114 | CHST115 | CHST154Y | CHST138 | CHST190 | CHST199 | ENVS131 | PSYC134 | PSYC172)', '[]', '[]', 'Students must also fulfill undergraduate Core Curriculum requirements for the Bachelor of Science degree.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/child-studies.html#07937c069e5d'),
('Individual Studies', 'Students design an individualized interdisciplinary curriculum approved by a faculty advisor. The plan must demonstrate curricular diversity, rely primarily on existing courses, and may include up to four study‐abroad courses.', '', 0, '', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Eligibility Requirements","requirementDescription":"Be a full-time student at Santa Clara for at least one year; have fewer than 111 quarter units completed at time of application; maintain a minimum GPA of 3.0."},{"requirementName":"Petition Requirements","requirementDescription":"Submit a Petition for Admission to the ISP director, including: a clear and conceptually refined description of the proposed program; an argument demonstrating that no existing major meets the student’s objectives; a plan of study listing courses, seminars, internships, etc., that fulfills Core Curriculum and educational goals; and identification of a faculty advisor whose expertise aligns with the proposed area of study."}]', 'Students should begin by scheduling a meeting with the program director to obtain a list of administrative instructions and guidance.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/individual-studies.html#37d707d78140'),
('Physics', 'The traditional physics major provides a strong foundation in chemistry, mathematics, and core physics, followed by selection of either the traditional physics track or the biophysics track.', 'PHYS', 1, '(CHEM11 | CHEM14) & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14) & (MATH23 | AMTH106) & ((PHYS31 & PHYS32) | (PHYS11 & PHYS12)) & (PHYS33 & PHYS34 & PHYS70 & PHYS103 & PHYS111 & PHYS192)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"GPA approval","requirementDescription":"A student whose GPA is below 2.5 must obtain approval from the department chair to declare a Physics or Engineering Physics major."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/physics.html#6598cf74a8fa'),
('Engineering Physics', 'The engineering physics major combines physics fundamentals with mathematics and engineering courses, emphasizing preparation for research, development, and graduate study in applied physics and engineering disciplines.', 'PHYS', 0, '(CHEM11 | CHEM14) & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14) & (AMTH106 | MATH23) & 1(CSCI10 | COEN10 | COEN11 | MECH45) & (PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33 & PHYS34 & PHYS70 & PHYS103 & PHYS111 & PHYS112 & PHYS192) & (PHYS120 | MECH121) & 1(PHYS104 | PHYS113 | PHYS116 | PHYS122 | PHYS123 | PHYS151 | PHYS161 | PHYS162 | PHYS171) & 4(CHEM12 | MECH10 | MECH11 | MECH15 | MECH122 | MECH143 | ELEN123 | COEN123 | CENG41 | CENG43 | COEN11 | CSCI60 | ELEN21 | COEN21 | ELEN100 | ELEN110 | ELEN115 | ELEN118 | ELEN144)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Technical course cluster","requirementDescription":"An approved cluster of five additional technical courses focused in a specific area chosen by the student and subject to advisor consent."},{"requirementName":"GPA approval","requirementDescription":"A student whose GPA is below 2.5 must obtain approval from the department chair to declare a Physics or Engineering Physics major."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/physics.html#6598cf74a8fa'),
