('Biochemistry, ACS Certified', 'ACS-certified biochemistry track with the full ACS chemistry and biochemistry sequence, required research seminars, two electives (one may be a biology course), seminar, math and physics support, and BIOL 1A–C & 175.', 'CHEM', 0, '((CHEM11 & CHEM12) | CHEM14) & (CHEM31 & CHEM32 & CHEM33 & CHEM50) & (CHEM101 & CHEM111 & CHEM141 & CHEM142 & CHEM143 & CHEM150 & CHEM151 & CHEM152 & CHEM154) & CHEM15 & (CHEM183 & CHEM184) & 2((CHEM100-199 | BIOL110 | BIOL113 | BIOL172 | BIOL174 | BIOL178) & !(CHEM182)) & 4(CHEM115) & ((MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13) | (MATH35 & MATH36 & MATH13)) & (PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33) & (BIOL1A & BIOL1B & BIOL1C & BIOL175)', '[]', '[]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/chemistry-and-biochemistry.html#cb812009d91c'),
('Chemistry', 'Liberal-arts–oriented chemistry program with core chemistry courses, two upper-division electives, a 30-hour lab requirement, seminar, and supporting math and physics sequences.', 'CHEM', 0, '((CHEM11 & CHEM12) | CHEM14) & (CHEM31 & CHEM32 & CHEM33 & CHEM50) & ((CHEM101 | CHEM102) & CHEM111 & CHEM141 & (CHEM150 | CHEM151 | CHEM152)) & CHEM15 & 2(CHEM100-199 & !(CHEM182)) & 4(CHEM115) & ((MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13) | (MATH35 & MATH36 & MATH13)) & ((PHYS11 & PHYS12 & PHYS13) | (PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Upper-division lab","requirementDescription":"30 laboratory contact hours, which may be satisfied by CHEM 102, CHEM 143, CHEM 154, or 1 unit of CHEM 182."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/chemistry-and-biochemistry.html#cb812009d91c'),
('Economics', 'The economics major provides rigorous, systematic analysis of economic issues including wealth and poverty, unemployment, inflation, international trade, and economic growth, preparing students for careers in private and public sectors and for graduate study.', 'ECON', 0, '((ECON1 | ECON1E) & ECON2 & ECON3) & ((MATH11 & MATH12) | (MATH30 & MATH31)) & (OMIS40 | MATH122 | MATH8 | AMTH108) & (ECON41 & ECON42) & (ECON113 & ECON114 & ECON115 & (ECON181 | ECON182)) & 5(ECON100-199)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core Curriculum","requirementDescription":"In addition to departmental requirements, students must complete undergraduate Core Curriculum and College of Arts and Sciences requirements for the bachelor of science degree."},{"requirementName":"Elective sequencing","requirementDescription":"At least two of the upper-division economics electives must be completed after ECON 113 and ECON 115."},{"requirementName":"Prerequisite","requirementDescription":"A grade of C- or better in ECON 1, 2, and 3 is required for all upper-division economics courses."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/economics.html#c89c2dd151c8'),
('Psychology', 'The Department of Psychology offers a degree program leading to the bachelor of science in psychology. Psychology is the study of behavior, emotion, and thought using the scientific method. At the undergraduate level, the study of psychology is part of a liberal arts education. A major in psychology lays the groundwork for various careers and advanced studies, including the pursuit of graduate degrees needed for the professional practice of psychology.', 'PSYC', 0, '(PSYC1 & PSYC2 & PSYC51 & PSYC52 & PSYC53 & (MATH8 & (MATH6 | MATH35 | MATH11)) & 1(PSYC165 | PSYC166 | PSYC167) & 1(PSYC172 | PSYC184 | PSYC185 | PSYC196) & 1(PSYC115 | PSYC117 | PSYC134 | PSYC140 | PSYC157 | PSYC158) & 1(PSYC150 | PSYC160 | PSYC162) & 1(PSYC120 | PSYC130 | PSYC131 | PSYC138) & 1(PSYC111 | PSYC116 | PSYC118 | PSYC132 | PSYC133 | PSYC141 | PSYC151 | PSYC154 | PSYC168 | PSYC175 | PSYC178 | PSYC199A) & 3(PSYC100-199))', '[]', '[]', 'Psychology majors may be selected for graduation with Honors in Psychology provided they have a grade point average of 3.3 or higher in their psychology courses, complete PSYC 99 and a senior project in a manner approved by the faculty honors committee. Honors students are expected to participate in various department-sponsored events.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/psychology.html#cbd09cb3c353'),
('Environmental Science', 'A BS curriculum integrating chemistry, biology, physics, math, and environmental science courses with social science and field experiences, culminating in a 100-hour internship.', 'ENVS', 0, '(ENVS21 & ENVS22 & ENVS23 & (MATH11 | MATH35) & CHEM11 & CHEM12 & CHEM31 & (ENVS79 | PHIL29) & ENVS100 & ENVS101 & ENVS122 & ENVS198 & (ENVS110 | BIOL160) & (ENVS116 | CENG160) & ENVS188 & (BIOL1A | BIOL1B | BIOL1C | PHYS11 | PHYS12 | PHYS13 | PHYS31 | PHYS32 | PHYS33))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Social science elective","requirementDescription":"One selection from the approved list of departmental upper-division social science courses"},{"requirementName":"Environmental science electives","requirementDescription":"Six upper-division environmental science courses: at least two from biological sciences, at least two from physical sciences, up to two elective courses; at least three must be lab courses"},{"requirementName":"Internship","requirementDescription":"An approved 100-hour internship"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/environmental-studies-and-sciences.html#85643ab4ddbb'),
('Environmental Studies', 'A BS curriculum emphasizing interdisciplinary environmental perspectives, combining core ESS courses with social science, methods, ethics, field electives, and a 100-hour internship.', 'ENVS', 0, '(ENVS21 & ENVS22 & ENVS23 & (ANTH50 | ENVS50) & (ENVS79 | PHIL29) & ENVS100 & ENVS101 & ENVS122 & ENVS198 & ENVS111 & (ENVS116 | CENG160) & ENVS188)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Statistics elective","requirementDescription":"One selection from the approved list of statistics courses (ENVS 110 preferred)"},{"requirementName":"Environmental studies electives","requirementDescription":"Five upper-division courses: one natural science lab course from departmental electives; two to four additional departmental electives; up to two electives outside the department"},{"requirementName":"Internship","requirementDescription":"An approved 100-hour internship"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/environmental-studies-and-sciences.html#85643ab4ddbb'),
('management information systems', 'The management information systems major focuses on the design, implementation, and evaluation of information systems and analytical decision-making methods in organizations.', 'OMIS', 0, '(OMIS30 & OMIS105 & OMIS106 & OMIS107 & 3(OMIS111 | OMIS112 | OMIS113 | OMIS114 | OMIS116 | OMIS117 | OMIS118 | OMIS120 | OMIS135 | OMIS137 | OMIS150))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Double-dipping prohibition","requirementDescription":"A course cannot be double-dipped in multiple programs."}]', 'The MIS major is STEM-designated.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/information-systems-analytics.html#25ebf5158560'),
('accounting and information systems', 'The accounting and information systems major integrates accounting coursework with information systems and analytics, preparing students for careers in systems administration, management consulting, and technical roles.', '', 0, '(ACTG120 & ACTG130 & ACTG131 & ACTG132 & ACTG135 & ACTG136 & ACTG138 & OMIS30 & OMIS105 & OMIS106 & (OMIS150 | ACTG155) & (OMIS107 | OMIS111 | OMIS113 | OMIS114 | OMIS120 | OMIS135 | OMIS137))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Double-dipping prohibition","requirementDescription":"A course cannot be double-dipped in multiple programs."}]', 'The AIS major is STEM-designated.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/information-systems-analytics.html#25ebf5158560'),
('Neuroscience', 'The neuroscience major equips students with interdisciplinary insights into the nervous system’s structure and function, ethical considerations in research, and prepares them for diverse careers or graduate study.', 'NEUR', 0, '(NEUR1 & NEUR10 & NEUR150 & NEUR190) & (BIOL1A & BIOL1B & BIOL1C & BIOL122 & BIOL160) & (CHEM11 & (CHEM12 | CHEM14) & CHEM31 & CHEM32 & CHEM33) & (MATH35 | MATH11) & (MATH36 | MATH12 | CSCI10) & (PSYC1 & PSYC165 & PSYC169) & 1(BIOL110 | BIOL112 | BIOL120 | BIOL123 | BIOL124 | BIOL165 | BIOL172 | BIOL174 | BIOL175 | BIOL178) & 1(NEUR185 | PSYC120 | PSYC130 | PSYC138 | PSYC166 | PSYC167 | PSYC196) & 1(BIOL110 | BIOL112 | BIOL119 | BIOL120 | BIOL123 | BIOL123A | BIOL124 | BIOL165 | BIOL171 | BIOL172 | BIOL174 | BIOL175 | BIOL178 | CHEM141 | CSCI168) & 1(COMM176A | COMM113 | PHIL113 | PHIL117 | NEUR185 | PSYC120 | PSYC130 | PSYC138 | PSYC166 | PSYC167 | PSYC196)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core Curriculum","requirementDescription":"Must complete the undergraduate Core Curriculum requirements for the bachelor of science degree."}]', 'PHIL 32 is recommended.
