('Public Health Science', 'An interdisciplinary degree focused on the health of human populations and individuals, exploring structural, social, environmental, and biological determinants of health through core and elective courses, a senior capstone, and a 100-hour internship.', 'PHSC', 1, '(PHSC1 & PHSC2 & PHSC3 & PHSC100 & PHSC139 & PHSC150 & PHSC190 & PHSC197)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"100-Hour Internship","requirementDescription":"Complete at least 100 hours of public health-related internship work approved in advance by a Public Health faculty member."}]', 'Students intending to pursue medical or other health-professional training should consult the University pre-health advisor regarding additional prerequisites (e.g., full year of physics and organic chemistry).', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/public-health-department.html#509f0dd05b17'),
('Finance', 'Development of knowledge and managerial skills in corporate and investment settings, preparing graduates for careers as corporate financial officers, traders, investment managers, financial analysts, planners, bankers, stockbrokers, regulators, and other specialties.', 'FNCE', 0, '(FNCE124 & FNCE125 & (MATH12 | MATH31 | FNCE186) & 4((FNCE100-199) & !(FNCE118 | FNCE127 | FNCE129 | FNCE131)))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core and College Requirements","requirementDescription":"In addition to fulfilling undergraduate Core Curriculum and Leavey School of Business requirements for the bachelor of science in commerce degree."},{"requirementName":"Elective Qualification Note","requirementDescription":"FNCE 186 qualifies as one of the four upper-division finance electives; FNCE 118, FNCE 127, FNCE 129, and FNCE 131 do not satisfy upper-division elective requirements for finance majors and are not included in the finance major GPA."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/finance.html#7428eed349a9'),
('General Engineering', 'Bachelor of Science in Engineering requiring foundational courses in English, mathematics, natural sciences, core engineering, a design sequence, and electives defining a coherent technical concentration.', 'ENGR', 0, '(ENGL181) & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & AMTH106 & AMTH108 & CHEM11 & CHEM11L & PHYS31 & PHYS31L & PHYS32 & PHYS32L & PHYS33 & PHYS33L) & (ENGR1 & ENGR1L & ENGR2 & ENGR110 & BIOE111 & CENG41 & CENG43 & CENG43L & CSEN10 & CSEN10L & ECEN21 & ECEN21L & ECEN50 & ECEN50L & ECEN115 & ECEN115L & MECH10L & MECH11 & MECH15 & MECH15L & MECH121) & (ENGR193 | ENGR197A) & (ENGR163A & ENGR163B) & (ENGR194 | ENGR195 | ENGR196 | ENGR197B | ENGR197C | ENGR197D)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Electives: coherent technical concentration","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":36,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Mathematics elective","requirementDescription":"AMTH108 or other approved upper-division mathematics elective"},{"requirementName":"Alternative design options","requirementDescription":"With permission, may choose one of: BIOE194, BIOE195, BIOE196; CENG192A, CENG192B, CENG192C, CENG193, CENG194; CSEN194, CSEN195, CSEN196; ECEN194, ECEN195, ECEN196; MECH194, MECH195, MECH196"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/general-engineering.html#f9a9769c11c2'),
('Accounting', 'Requires completion of ACTG 120 and the core accounting courses ACTG 130, 131, 132, 134, 135, 136, and 138.', 'ACTG', 0, '(ACTG120 & ACTG130 & ACTG131 & ACTG132 & ACTG134 & ACTG135 & ACTG136 & ACTG138)', '[]', '[]', 'Accounting majors may use ACTG 134 to satisfy both the information systems requirement in the Leavey School of Business curriculum and the Science, Technology & Society requirement in the 2009 University Core.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/accounting.html#88aede57b843'),
('Accounting and Information Systems', 'Combines accounting and information systems coursework, requiring core accounting courses, OMIS information-systems courses, and an OMIS elective. This joint major has STEM designation effective September 2023.', 'ACTG', 0, '(ACTG120 & ACTG130 & ACTG131 & ACTG132 & ACTG135 & ACTG136 & ACTG138 & OMIS30 & OMIS105 & OMIS106 & ACTG155 & 1(OMIS107 | OMIS111 | OMIS113 | OMIS114 | OMIS120 | OMIS135 | OMIS137))', '[]', '[]', 'Accounting and information systems majors may use OMIS 30 to satisfy the information systems requirement in the Leavey School of Business curriculum.
OMIS 150 is cross-listed with ACTG 155.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/accounting.html#88aede57b843'),
('Mathematics', 'Bachelor of Science in Mathematics preparing students for graduate study, secondary teaching, or research careers, with optional emphases in applied mathematics, data science, financial mathematics, mathematical economics, and mathematics education.', 'MATH', 0, 'CSCI10 & MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & MATH23 & MATH51 & MATH52 & MATH53 & PHYS31 & PHYS32 & 7((MATH101-189 | CSCI162) & (MATH102 | MATH105 | MATH153) & (MATH103 | MATH111) & (MATH101 | MATH113 | MATH174 | MATH176 | MATH177 | MATH122 | MATH125 | MATH141 | MATH144 | MATH146 | MATH155 | MATH166))', '[{"requirementDescription":"Required upper-division courses in the major taken at Santa Clara","measuredBy":"courses","numRequired":4,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":4,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Programming proficiency","requirementDescription":"Demonstrated equivalent proficiency in computer programming may substitute for CSCI 10"},{"requirementName":"Physics substitution","requirementDescription":"ECON 170 or 173 may substitute for PHYS 32; with department approval PHYS 11 and 12 may substitute for PHYS 31 and 32"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/mathematics-and-computer-science.html#4d8620d8dfad'),
('Computer Science', 'Bachelor of Science in Computer Science preparing students for graduate study, secondary teaching, or research careers, with optional emphases in algorithms and complexity, data science, security, software, or a student-designed emphasis.', 'CSCI', 1, 'CSCI10 & CSCI60 & CSCI61 & CSCI62 & MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & MATH51 & MATH53 & (PHYS31 | CHEM11 | ENVS21 | ENVS23) & CSEN20 & CSEN20L & CSEN21 & CSEN21L & MATH122 & CSCI161 & CSCI163 & CSEN177 & CSEN177L', '[{"requirementDescription":"Required upper-division courses in the major taken at Santa Clara","measuredBy":"courses","numRequired":4,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":4,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[]', 'Although CSCI 10 is not explicitly listed as a formal prerequisite, some upper-division courses require programming ability
A single upper-division course may not be used to satisfy requirements for two majors or minors without approval
Students should decide their emphasis by the end of junior year; only one emphasis is allowed and Data Science may not be used for both majors', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/mathematics-and-computer-science.html#4d8620d8dfad'),
('Gender and Sexuality Studies', 'An interdisciplinary major requiring foundational principles courses, required upper-division courses, a three-course concentration in one of three thematic areas, and electives.', 'WGST', 1, '1(WGST1A & WGST2A | WGST11A & WGST12A | WGST25 | WGST50 | WGST51 | WGST52 | WGST59 | ETHN59 | WGST112 | ETHN154) & (WGST101 & WGST102 & WGST105 & WGST190)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Total courses required for the major","measuredBy":"courses","numRequired":13,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Concentration","requirementDescription":"A three-course concentration in one of three areas: Cultural Politics of Representation; Power, Rights, and Society; or Sexualities, Body Politics, and Social Structures."},{"requirementName":"Electives","requirementDescription":"Five electives."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/gender-and-sexuality-studies.html#81c027c34540'),
('Classics', 'Bachelor of Arts in Classics requiring selection of one of three tracks: Classical Languages and Literatures, Classical Studies, or Ancient Studies.', 'CLAS', 1, '', '[]', '[]', 'Approved courses include all classes with the CLAS prefix, as well as courses in other departments such as ARTH 104, 106, 110; ARTH 152 may count for the Ancient Studies track; PHIL 14, 141; POLI 111. Other ancient world courses may count with department chair approval. A classical language class may substitute for a non-language course with approval.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/classics.html#23ebc4ecf83a'),
('Civil Engineering', 'Bachelor of Science in Civil Engineering requiring core curriculum plus a minimum of 195 units, including required courses in English, mathematics, natural sciences, engineering fundamentals, and technical electives.', 'CENG', 0, 'ENGL181 & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14) & (AMTH106 & (AMTH112 | AMTH108)) & (CHEM11 | CHEM11T) & (PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33) & (CENG20 & CENG20L) & (ENGR1 & ENGR1L) & (ECEN49 | (ECEN50 & ECEN50L)) & (CENG7 & CENG7L & CENG10 & CENG10L & CENG15 & CENG41 & CENG44A & CENG44AL & CENG44B & CENG115 & CENG115L & CENG121 & CENG121L & CENG125 & CENG125L & CENG128 & CENG132 & CENG140 & CENG140L & CENG141 & CENG141L & CENG143 & CENG143L & CENG145 & CENG148 & CENG148L & CENG192A & CENG192B & CENG192C & CENG193 & CENG194 & (CENG160 | CENG182)) & (2(CENG122 | CENG133 | CENG134 | CENG135 | CENG135L | CENG136 | CENG137 | CENG138 | CENG142 | CENG144 | CENG144L | CENG146 | CENG147 | CENG150) & 1(CENG118 | CENG119 | CENG122 | CENG123 | CENG123L | CENG124 | CENG137 | CENG139 | CENG149 | CENG151 | CENG160 | CENG161 | CENG162 | CENG182 | CENG184 | CENG185 | CENG186 | CENG187) & 1(CENG122 | CENG133 | CENG134 | CENG135 | CENG135L | CENG136 | CENG137 | CENG138 | CENG142 | CENG144 | CENG144L | CENG146 | CENG147 | CENG150 | CENG118 | CENG119 | CENG122 | CENG123 | CENG123L | CENG124 | CENG137 | CENG139 | CENG149 | CENG151 | CENG160 | CENG161 | CENG162 | CENG182 | CENG184 | CENG185 | CENG186 | CENG187))', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units for major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":195,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Free elective","requirementDescription":"One free elective (4 units)"}]', 'Combined BS/MS program: undergraduates may begin master’s coursework between February of junior year and December of senior year, complete 46 units beyond the bachelor’s degree (up to 20 may be taken as an undergraduate), and must satisfy all graduate requirements.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/civil-environmental-and-sustainable-engineering.html#ebcacb23ca46'),
('Sociology', 'The Sociology major equips students to engage in positive social change and develop a sociological imagination through a combination of foundational courses, theory, methods, and electives.', 'SOCI', 0, '(SOCI1 & SOCI35 & SOCI118 & SOCI119 & SOCI120 & SOCI198 & (SOCI121 | SOCI122) & (8((SOCI100-199) & !(SOCI118 | SOCI119 | SOCI120 | SOCI121 | SOCI122 | SOCI198)) | (7((SOCI100-199) & !(SOCI118 | SOCI119 | SOCI120 | SOCI121 | SOCI122 | SOCI198)) & 1(SOCI30 | SOCI33 | SOCI49 | SOCI60 | SOCI65 | SOCI91 | SOCI99))))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core Curriculum Requirements","requirementDescription":"In addition to fulfilling undergraduate Core Curriculum requirements for the bachelor of science degree."}]', 'Students may also choose to concentrate in one or more concentrations in the major. See the department website for more information.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/sociology.html#52e73cfac556'),
('English', 'The English major centers on literature, cultural studies, and writing, integrating critical, professional, and creative writing projects into every course. Students explore British, American, and global literature, professional communication, new media, and film through diverse theoretical approaches.', 'ENGL', 0, '(ENGL14 & ENGL15 & ENGL16)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Historically grounded literary or cultural studies courses","requirementDescription":"Two courses; at least one from a period before 1800"},{"requirementName":"Concentration in literary/cultural studies","requirementDescription":"Three courses (American, British, Global, or individually defined); at least two upper-division"},{"requirementName":"Concentration in writing","requirementDescription":"Three courses in professional writing and new media, or creative writing, or individually defined; at least two upper-division"},{"requirementName":"Upper-division theory/gender/sexuality/ethnic/global studies course","requirementDescription":"One upper-division course (may also be used to meet another requirement)"},{"requirementName":"Senior seminar","requirementDescription":"One senior seminar"},{"requirementName":"Course challenge policy","requirementDescription":"English Department does not allow students to challenge courses"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/english.html#efe14a4896d1'),
('Management', 'The management major prepares students to analyze complex business problems within organizational environments and apply effective strategies while developing ethical reasoning, leadership, interpersonal, communication, teamwork, and group dynamics skills.', 'MGMT', 0, '(MGMT174 & 4(MGMT110 | MGMT164 | MGMT165 | MGMT166 | MGMT168 | MGMT169 | MGMT170 | MGMT171 | MGMT172 | MGMT173 | MGMT175 | MGMT176 | MGMT177 | MGMT178 | MGMT179 | MGMT180 | MGMT181 | MGMT197 | MGMT198 | MGMT198E | MGMT199))', '[]', '[]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/management.html#0ee82f124271'),
('Political Science', 'The political science major introduces students to the analysis of political behavior, values, institutions, and governments, preparing them for graduate study and careers in public service, research, nonprofits, and the private sector. It integrates practical field experience through internships and offers study abroad opportunities.', 'POLI', 0, '1(MATH8 | MATH11 | MATH30 | MATH35) & (POLI1 & POLI2 & POLI25 & POLI30 & (POLI40 | ECON1 | ECON2) & POLI99) & 7(POLI100-199)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core Curriculum","requirementDescription":"Completion of the undergraduate Core Curriculum requirements for the Bachelor of Science degree"},{"requirementName":"Subfield distribution","requirementDescription":"One upper-division lecture course from four of the five subfields: United States politics, comparative politics, international relations, political philosophy, and applied quantitative methods"},{"requirementName":"Upper-division electives","requirementDescription":"Two additional upper-division political science electives, one of which may be a 5-unit internship course"},{"requirementName":"Senior seminar","requirementDescription":"Completion of a political science senior seminar after achieving senior status or with instructor permission"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/political-science.html#f2580432317e'),
('Electrical Engineering', 'The B.S. in Electrical Engineering (190 units) includes courses in English, mathematics, natural sciences, engineering fundamentals, ECEN core courses, technical electives across multiple focus areas, and a professional development experience.', 'ECEN', 0, '(ENGL181 & MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & AMTH106 & AMTH108 & (CHEM11 | CHEM11T) & PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33 & (PHYS34 | MATH51) & (CHEM12 | PHYS113 | PHYS121 | MATH53 | MATH105 | MATH123) & ENGR1 & CSEN10 & CSEN11 & CSEN12 & MECH121 & ECEN20 & ECEN21 & ECEN50 & ECEN100 & ECEN104 & ECEN110 & ECEN115 & ECEN120 & ECEN192 & ECEN194 & ECEN195 & ECEN196)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units for the major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":190,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Programming proficiency","requirementDescription":"Demonstrated equivalent programming proficiency satisfies CSEN 10 requirement"},{"requirementName":"Technical electives distribution","requirementDescription":"Five ECEN 100-level elective courses selected from specified areas, with one from at least four of the five areas; ECEN 188 and ECEN 189 may not be used"},{"requirementName":"Professional development","requirementDescription":"Completion of a professional development experience selected from options such as study abroad, cooperative education, ENGR 110, additional graduate-level coursework, approved minor or second major, combined BS/MS units, peer education, or undergraduate research (ECEN 199)"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/electrical-and-computer-engineering.html#95e2098e168c'),
('Electrical and Computer Engineering', 'The B.S. in Electrical and Computer Engineering (190 units) includes courses in English, mathematics, natural sciences, computer science, engineering fundamentals, ECEN core courses, technical electives, and a professional development experience.', 'ECEN', 0, '(ENGL181 & MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & MATH51 & MATH53 & CSCI163 & AMTH106 & AMTH108 & PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33 & (CHEM11 | CHEM12 | PHYS34 | PHYS113 | PHYS121 | MATH105 | MATH123) & ENGR1 & CSEN10 & CSEN11 & CSEN12 & CSEN177 & ECEN20 & ECEN21 & ECEN50 & ECEN100 & ECEN115 & ECEN120 & ECEN121 & ECEN122 & ECEN133 & ECEN142 & ECEN192 & ECEN194 & ECEN195 & ECEN196)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units for the major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":190,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Technical electives","requirementDescription":"Three ECEN 100-level elective courses approved by advisor, with at least one from ECEN 123, 127, 131, 162, 180; at most one may be from CSEN; ECEN 188 and 189 may not be used"},{"requirementName":"Professional development","requirementDescription":"Completion of a professional development experience selected from options such as study abroad, cooperative education, ENGR 110, additional graduate-level coursework, approved minor or second major, combined BS/MS units, peer education, or undergraduate research (ECEN 199)"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/electrical-and-computer-engineering.html#95e2098e168c'),
('Bioengineering', 'The major in bioengineering is designed to prepare students for careers in the medical device, biotechnology and biopharmaceutical industries, graduate study in bioengineering, or entry into medical school.', 'BIOE', 1, '(ENGL181 & (BIOE180 | BIOL171 | ENGR19 | PHIL27 | PHIL117 | TESP157) & MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14 & AMTH106 & (BIOE120 | AMTH108) & ENGR1 & ENGR1L & BIOE1 & BIOE23 & BIOE24 & BIOE25 & BIOE45 & BIOE194 & BIOE195 & BIOE196)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units required for the major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":191,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"BIOE100 repeat limit","requirementDescription":"BIOE100 can only be taken up to two times."},{"requirementName":"Co-op and research unit limit","requirementDescription":"Maximum of 6 units combined for co-ops, internships, and supervised independent research. Non-BIOE units will not be credited."}]', 'The course not selected as a required course may count as a TE.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/bioengineering.html#9cccaee2d064'),
('Ethnic Studies', 'The Ethnic Studies major provides advanced, concentrated training in critical racial and ethnic studies. Upper-division coursework is organized around six thematic clusters—Community Engagement & Social Movements; Race, Law, Politics & Policy; Intersectionality & Hybridity; Inequality & Education; Immigration, Transnationalism & Globalization; and Social & Cultural Analysis—and culminates in a methods seminar and a capstone research project.', 'ETHN', 0, 'ETHN5 & 2(ETHN10 | ETHN20 | ETHN30 | ETHN40 | ETHN80) & (ANTH86 | ANTH90 | DANC62 | ENGL35 | ENGL35G | ENGL36 | ENGL37 | ENGL38 | ENGL39 | ENGL69AM | ETHN11 | ETHN12 | ETHN13 | ETHN21 | ETHN22 | ETHN25 | ETHN35 | ETHN36 | ETHN41 | ETHN50 | ETHN51 | ETHN55 | ETHN59 | ETHN60 | ETHN65 | ETHN69 | ETHN70 | ETHN75 | ETHN81 | ETHN90 | ETHN95 | ETHN96 | MUSC20 | RSOC91 | THTR14 | THTR65) & 6(ETHN100 | ETHN101 | ETHN102 | ETHN111 | ETHN112 | ETHN120 | ETHN121 | ETHN122 | ETHN123 | ETHN124 | ETHN125 | ETHN125A | ETHN126 | ETHN127 | ETHN128 | ETHN129 | ETHN130 | ETHN130A | ETHN130H | ETHN131 | ETHN132 | ETHN132A | ETHN133 | ETHN135 | ETHN136 | ETHN137 | ETHN138 | ETHN138A | ETHN139 | ETHN141 | ETHN142 | ETHN144 | ETHN145 | ETHN149 | ETHN150 | ETHN151 | ETHN152 | ETHN153 | ETHN154 | ETHN154A | ETHN155 | ETHN157 | ETHN160 | ETHN161 | ETHN162 | ETHN163 | ETHN164 | ETHN166 | ETHN167 | ETHN168 | ETHN169 | ETHN170 | ETHN171 | ETHN172 | ETHN174 | ETHN175 | ETHN178 | ETHN180 | ETHN196 | ETHN197) & (ETHN165 | ETHN195) & ETHN198', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Upper-division elective","requirementDescription":"One upper-division elective, which may be an ETHN course or a course from an approved list in any other department or program."},{"requirementName":"Capstone research project option","requirementDescription":"Completion of a research project in an upper-division ethnic studies seminar as an alternative to ETHN 198."},{"requirementName":"Category distribution","requirementDescription":"Six upper-division courses must be selected from at least four of the six thematic categories."},{"requirementName":"Category overlap restriction","requirementDescription":"No course may be used to satisfy more than one category; any exception requires approval of the department chair."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/ethnic-studies.html#db9bedbcbb32'),
('Economics', 'The Economics major builds core theoretical and quantitative skills through foundational economics courses, a math prerequisite, and upper-division electives.', 'ECON', 0, '(ECON41 & ECON42) & (ECON113 & ECON114 & ECON115 & (ECON181 | ECON182)) & (MATH12 | MATH31) & 3(ECON100-199 & !(ECON113 | ECON114 | ECON115 | ECON181 | ECON182))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Core and Leavey School Requirements","requirementDescription":"Students must fulfill undergraduate Core Curriculum and Leavey School of Business requirements for the bachelor of science in commerce degree."},{"requirementName":"Prerequisite Grade Requirement","requirementDescription":"A grade of C- or better in ECON 1, ECON 2, and ECON 3 is required for all upper-division economics courses."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/economics.html#0b4e62ee6c48'),
('Music', 'Bachelor of Arts in Music requiring completion of theory sequences, listening series, Music at Noon attendance, upper-division electives in general and in ethnomusicology/music history, an electronic music course, applied instruction, and ensemble participation.', 'MUSC', 0, '(MUSC1&MUSC2&MUSC3)&(MUSC1A&MUSC2A&MUSC3A)&2(MUSC7|MUSC8|MUSC9|MUSC10)&(MUSC16|MUSC116)&5(MUSC100-199)&1(MUSC114|MUSC124|MUSC127|MUSC130|MUSC131|MUSC132|MUSC133|MUSC134|MUSC135|MUSC136|MUSC139|MUSC189|MUSC190|MUSC192|MUSC194|MUSC195|MUSC196)&1(MUSC9|MUSC115|MUSC119|MUSC157)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Applied instruction","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":6,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"MUSC"},{"requirementDescription":"Approved department ensemble","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":12,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"MUSC"}]', '[]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/music.html#98b1758c5b3d'),
('French and Francophone Studies', 'Bachelor of Arts in French and Francophone studies.', 'FREN', 0, '(FREN100 & FREN101)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Electives in French and Francophone studies","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":40,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":20,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"FREN"}]', '[{"requirementName":"French literature requirement","requirementDescription":"At least one course in French and Francophone literatures"},{"requirementName":"Substitution policy","requirementDescription":"Department-approved substitutions allowed for FREN 100 and 101"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/modern-languages-and-literatures.html#0fe0bb2f41c3'),
('Italian Studies', 'Bachelor of Arts in Italian studies.', 'ITAL', 0, '(ITAL100 & ITAL101)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Electives in Italian language, literature, and culture","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":40,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":20,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"ITAL"}]', '[{"requirementName":"Substitution policy","requirementDescription":"Department-approved substitutions allowed for ITAL 100 and 101"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/modern-languages-and-literatures.html#0fe0bb2f41c3'),
('Spanish Studies', 'Bachelor of Arts in Spanish studies.', 'SPAN', 0, '', '[{"requirementDescription":"Spanish courses to total 40 upper-division units","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":40,"typeRequired":"Upper Division","numRequiredFromSCU":20,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"SPAN"}]', '[{"requirementName":"Spanish major requirements","requirementDescription":"One course from 100 or 101 (including courses with a letter suffix); one course from 102 or 103; one course from 100 to 110 (not taken to fulfill the above two requirements); Spanish 175, 176, 177, or an advisor-approved equivalent; one course in literature and culture studies above 110; one additional course above 110 (not taken to fulfill the above requirements); any two upper-division Spanish courses not taken to satisfy any of the above requirements."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/modern-languages-and-literatures.html#0fe0bb2f41c3'),
('Marketing', 'The Marketing major prepares students for careers in general management or specialized marketing fields by requiring foundational courses MKTG 182 and 183 plus three marketing electives.', 'MKTG', 0, '(MKTG182 & MKTG183 & 3(MKTG165 | MKTG175 | MKTG177 | MKTG178 | MKTG185 | MKTG186 | MKTG187 | MKTG188 | MKTG189 | MKTG190 | MKTG191 | MKTG194))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Cross-listed course requirement","requirementDescription":"Students must take MKTG 179 or BUSN 179, which are cross-listed and required for all majors."},{"requirementName":"Internship substitution limitation","requirementDescription":"MKTG 198 cannot be substituted for an elective course in the major."}]', 'An emphasis will not appear on a student''s transcript.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/marketing.html#5e445d7bc235'),
('Theatre Arts', 'Bachelor of Arts in Theatre Arts with emphases in Theatre or Dance, focusing on academic rigor, artistic discipline, and creative expression, culminating in a senior capstone project.', 'THTR', 1, '', '[]', '[]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/theatre-and-dance.html#8d7a022b0b40'),
('Computer Science and Engineering', 'The program covers foundational courses in mathematics, natural sciences, engineering and computer science, plus upper-division electives and educational enrichment experiences.', 'CSEN', 0, 'ENGL181 & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14) & AMTH106 & AMTH108 & (MATH53 | CSCI166 | AMTH118) & (CHEM11 | CHEM11T) & (PHYS31 & PHYS32 & PHYS33) & ENGR1 & (ECEN21 | ELEN21 | CSEN21 | COEN21) & (ECEN50 | ELEN50) & (ECEN153 | ELEN153) & CSEN10 & (CSEN11 | COEN11) & (CSEN12 | COEN12) & (CSEN19 | COEN19) & (CSEN20 | COEN20) & (CSEN79 | COEN79) & (CSEN122 | COEN122) & (CSEN146 | COEN146) & (CSEN171 | COEN171) & (CSEN174 | COEN174) & (CSEN175 | COEN175) & (CSEN177 | COEN177) & (CSEN179 | COEN179) & (CSEN192 | COEN192) & (CSEN194 | COEN194 | ENGR194) & (CSEN195 | COEN195 | ENGR195) & (CSEN196 | COEN196 | ENGR196) & 3(CSEN101-180 | COEN101-180 | ECEN115 | ELEN115 | ECEN133 | ELEN133)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units for major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":192,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Programming proficiency substitution","requirementDescription":"Demonstrated equivalent programming proficiency may be substituted for CSEN/COEN 10"},{"requirementName":"Advisor-approved mathematics and science electives","requirementDescription":"Pre-approved replacements for CHEM 11: AP Biology (4–5), AP Environmental Science (4–5), BIOL 18, 21, 22, CHEM 1, ENVS 21, PHYS 34; substitutions for AMTH 106: CHEM 12, MATH 101–178, or any CHEM 11 replacement if not used to replace CHEM 11"},{"requirementName":"Elective substitution restrictions","requirementDescription":"6 units of CSEN/COEN 193 or 4 units of CSEN/COEN 199 may be used as one elective; at most one upper-division course from another department may be used as an elective with advisor approval; such courses cannot substitute for AMTH 106"},{"requirementName":"Educational Enrichment Electives","requirementDescription":"Select one: 8+ units in a study-abroad program; completion of ≥12 units in a master’s program; undergraduate research with ≥6 units of CSEN/COEN 193; or ≥12 units approved by an academic advisor in a single theme or department (not overlapping other major requirements)"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/computer-science-and-engineering.html#59ffa8ec905c'),
('Web Design and Engineering', 'This program combines computing education with courses in graphic art, communication, and sociology to address web infrastructure, societal impacts, and technological demands.', 'CSEN', 0, 'ENGL181 & ((ARTS74 | ARTS174) & (ARTS75 | ARTS175) & ARTS177) & ((COMM12 | COMM3 | COMM30) & COMM50) & (SOCI49 | SOCI149) & (MATH11 & MATH12 & MATH13 & MATH14) & AMTH108 & ENGR1 & (CSEN10 | COEN10 | CSCI10 | CSCI60 | CSCI61) & (CSEN11 | COEN11) & (CSEN12 | COEN12) & (CSEN60 | COEN60) & (CSEN146 | COEN146) & (CSEN161 | COEN161) & (CSEN162 | COEN162) & (CSEN163 | COEN163) & (CSEN164 | COEN164) & (CSEN169 | COEN169) & (CSEN174 | COEN174) & (CSEN192 | COEN192) & (CSEN194 | COEN194 | ENGR194) & (CSEN195 | COEN195 | ENGR195) & (CSEN196 | COEN196 | ENGR196)', '[{"requirementDescription":"Minimum total units for major","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":175,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":""}]', '[{"requirementName":"Natural Science elective","requirementDescription":"Any natural science course from the list approved by the University Core Curriculum"},{"requirementName":"Programming proficiency substitution","requirementDescription":"Demonstrated equivalent programming proficiency may be substituted for CSEN/COEN 10"},{"requirementName":"CSCI programming course alternatives","requirementDescription":"CSCI 10, CSCI 60, or CSCI 61 may substitute for programming coursework"},{"requirementName":"Educational Enrichment Electives","requirementDescription":"Select one: 8+ units in a study-abroad program; completion of ≥12 units in a master’s program; undergraduate research with ≥6 units of CSEN/COEN 193; or ≥12 units approved by an academic advisor"}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-5-school-of-engineering/computer-science-and-engineering.html#59ffa8ec905c'),
('Philosophy', 'The Bachelor of Arts in philosophy requires courses exploring introductory and historical philosophy, logic, metaphysics, epistemology, ethics, non-Western and specialized topics, plus additional upper-division electives to develop analytical thinking and precise expression.', 'PHIL', 0, '(PHIL40-45) & (PHIL14 & PHIL15 & PHIL16) & (PHIL17 | PHIL18) & PHIL19 & (PHIL124-127 | PHIL141A-151 | PHIL174-181A) & PHIL174-180 & (PHIL109-112 | PHIL120-129 | PHIL152 | PHIL154) & PHIL150-165 & 4(PHIL108-199)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Foundations Core Waiver","requirementDescription":"Requirement waived for students who completed a Foundations Core sequence in Philosophy (PHIL 1A/2A or PHIL 11A/12A)."},{"requirementName":"Mutual Exclusion","requirementDescription":"No one class may fulfill both the Non-Western Philosophy and the History of Philosophy requirement."},{"requirementName":"PHIL 199 Unit Requirement","requirementDescription":"To qualify as an upper-division elective, any PHIL 199 class must be 5 units."}]', 'To qualify for honors in philosophy, majors must maintain a 3.5 grade-point average in philosophy courses and complete PHIL 197 with a grade of A– or better.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/philosophy.html#2e5728c8beb5'),
('Religious Studies', 'A Bachelor of Arts program requiring lower‐division foundations in each of the three departmental areas and a range of upper‐division courses, including distribution and thematic requirements.', 'RELS', 0, '1(SCTR1-99) & 1(TESP1-99) & 1(RSOC1-99) & 8(RELS100-199) & 1(SCTR111 | SCTR111R | SCTR128 | TESP119 | TESP119R | TESP124 | TESP124R | TESP131 | WGST149 | TESP131R | WGST149R | TESP141 | TESP152 | TESP185 | TESP185R | TESP196 | TESP196R)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Seminar Requirement","requirementDescription":"Four of the eight upper-division courses must be seminars: one from each of the three areas (RSOC, SCTR, TESP) and RELS 190 Seminar in Interreligious Dialogue."}]', '', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/religious-studies.html#846b4ab8c333'),
('History', 'The History major provides an understanding of human experience through analysis of evidence from the past, developing analytical skills and geographical and thematic knowledge, preparing for a range of careers.', 'HIST', 0, '4(HIST1-99) & HIST100 & HIST101S & 6(HIST100-199 & !(HIST100 | HIST101S))', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Seminar course requirement","requirementDescription":"One seminar course taken after completing HIST 101S and 115 quarter units"},{"requirementName":"Distribution requirement","requirementDescription":"At least one course from four of the following six fields: Global History; United States and Canada; Latin America; Europe; East/South Asia; Africa/West Asia (excluding HIST 100 and 101S)"},{"requirementName":"Optional senior project","requirementDescription":"An optional senior project (HIST 197) may count as one of the required upper-division courses; required for eligibility for Honors in History"}]', 'Directed reading/research (HIST 199) is available with permission of the department chair and instructor
Hybrid courses are offered: lower-division hybrid courses are 4 units; upper-division hybrid courses are 5 units and require additional assignments', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/history.html#26de42993d7a'),
('Communication', 'The Communication major prepares students for careers in communication, entertainment, technology, journalism, and nonprofit sectors, as well as graduate studies. It emphasizes theories, research methods, and the integration of theory and practice by helping students apply their knowledge to create speeches, films, television programs, journalism, web content, and communication and marketing campaigns. Students complete foundation, intermediate, and upper-division courses and may choose one of six emphases or pursue a general program.', 'COMM', 0, '(COMM1 & COMM2 & COMM3 & COMM4) & 3(COMM10 | COMM30 | COMM50 | COMM60 | COMM80) & (COMM100 & COMM101 & COMM197) & 6(COMM102-189 | COMM198)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Prior-to-June-2022 major requirements","requirementDescription":"Students who declared the major prior to June 2022 may satisfy requirements with different course substitutions and course lists, as specified by the department."}]', 'All courses taken to fulfill requirements must be 4 or 5 units and taken for a letter grade; practicum courses numbered 190–195 do not count toward the major or minor.
Up to two approved study abroad courses may count toward communication upper-division electives.
Internships are encouraged for juniors and seniors and may count for department elective credit.
Students can pursue a general Communication degree or choose one of six emphases; completion of an emphasis is noted on transcripts.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/communication.html#fc3a72b696d8');

