('Data Analysis for Economics', 'Provides structured training in econometrics and data analysis applied to economic issues.', 'Major', 'Economics', 'ECON', 'ECON43 & (ECON173 | ECON174) & 3(ECON134 | ECON135 | ECON142 | ECON150 | ECON151 | ECON154 | ECON166 | ECON186 | ECON187 | ECON188 | ECON173 | ECON174)', '[]', '[{"requirementName":"Grade Requirement","requirementDescription":"Students must earn a grade of C or higher in all concentration courses."},{"requirementName":"Substitution Policy","requirementDescription":"One (and only one) of the courses in List C may be substituted with an approved course (CSCI183, ENVS117, OMIS114, or OMIS150) or an independent-study course with a substantial data-analysis component, with approval of the Concentration advisor. Non-economics courses will not count as upper-division electives toward the economics major."}]', 'All upper-division courses in the concentration can count as upper-division electives toward the economics major.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-4-leavey-school-of-business/economics.html#0b4e62ee6c48'),
