('Theatre', 'The Theatre emphasis provides courses in acting, design, theatre history/performance studies, dramatic literature, technical production, directing, and playwriting, culminating in a senior project demonstrating proficiency in a chosen area.', 'Major', 'Theatre Arts', 'THTR', '(THTR8 & THTR9 & THTR10 & THTR30 & (THTR31 | THTR32 | THTR33) & (DANC40 | DANC43 | DANC46) & THTR41 & THTR42 & (THTR112 | THTR113 | THTR119 | THTR151 | THTR161 | THTR163 | THTR165 | THTR167) & (DANC159 | DANC189) & THTR185 & (THTR192 | THTR193 | THTR195 | THTR196 | THTR197))', '[{"requirementDescription":"4 units of THTR 39/139","measuredBy":"units","numRequired":4,"typeRequired":"Any","numRequiredFromSCU":0,"mustBeFromDepartmentCode":"THTR"}]', '[{"requirementName":"Upper-division electives","requirementDescription":"Three approved 5-unit upper-division theatre or dance electives"}]', 'The Senior Project provides majors with the opportunity to demonstrate their progress in meeting the department learning objectives. In this capstone course, students prepare and present a final project in an area of their choosing, including public presentation, reflection on process, assessment of progress, and a culminating oral presentation.', 'https://www.scu.edu/bulletin/undergraduate/chapter-3-college-of-arts-and-sciences/theatre-and-dance.html#8d7a022b0b40'),
