('American Studies', 'American Studies is an interdisciplinary approach to the study of the United States, past and present. Students approach the study of American cultures through such diverse fields as history, literature, religious studies, art, economics, and environmental studies, and might focus on such topics as popular culture and material culture, ethnic studies and gender studies, empire and globalization. American Studies students analyze America''s relations with the rest of the world, the construction and deconstruction of American identities, and changing and competing definitions of America, including critiques of the very name "American Studies".', '["ANTH4","ANTH148","ANTH157","ANTH170","ARAB185","ARTH140","ARTH143","ARTH144","ARTH145","COMM136F","COMM138A","COMM166","ECON136","ENGL2A","ENGL31","ENGL32","ENGL33","ENGL35","ENGL36","ENGL37","ENGL38","ENGL39","ENGL39G","ENGL65","ENGL67","ENGL68","ENGL68A","ENGL69","ENGL69A","ENGL106","ENGL121","ENGL129","ENGL130","ENGL131","ENGL132","ENGL132G","ENGL133","ENGL134","ENGL134G","ENGL135","ENGL136","ENGL137","ENGL137G","ENGL138","ENGL139","ENGL139G","ENGL152","ENGL169","ENGL169A","ENGL192","ENVS20","ETHN5","ETHN12","ETHN21","ETHN30","ETHN36","ETHN40","ETHN65","ETHN69","ETHN70","ETHN95","ETHN96","ETHN111","ETHN124","ETHN130","ETHN132","ETHN134","ETHN135","ETHN136","ETHN137","ETHN138","ETHN141","ETHN142","ETHN145","ETHN151","ETHN152","ETHN153","ETHN164","ETHN166","ETHN176","ETHN185","GNSX15","GNSX16","GNSX34","GNSX50","GNSX56","GNSX57","GNSX110","GNSX111","GNSX115","GNSX117","GNSX136","GNSX138","GNSX144","GNSX155","GNSX156","GNSX164","GNSX165","GNSX166","GNSX173","GNSX174","GNSX174A","GNSX180","GNSX186","GOVT410","GOVT417","HIST60","HIST65","HIST70","HIST71","HIST72","HIST75","HIST82B","HIST84","HIST85","HIST86B","HIST96A","HIST96B","HIST105","HIST119","HIST155","HIST157","HIST158","HIST160","HIST165","HIST170","HIST171","HIST172","HIST174","HIST175","HIST176","HIST177","HIST181","HIST182B","HIST184","HIST185","HIST186","HIST188S","MILS176","MUSC20","MUSC21","MUSC132","MUSC134","PHIL33H","POLI1","POLI151","POLI153","POLI154","POLI163","POLI173","POLI195","POLI195DW","POLI195L","POLI195P","RSOC21","RSOC51","RSOC51H","RSOC61","RSOC91","RSOC111","RSOC111R","RSOC128","RSOC148","RSOC148R","RSOC164","RSOC175","RSOC184","SOCI33","SOCI132","SOCI150","SOCI153","SIS491","SPAN176","TESP60","TESP65","TESP109"]', 'https://www.scu.edu/provost/core/integrations/pathways/pathway-listings--courses/american-studies/'),
('Justice & the Arts', 'Courses that explore historical and contemporary works of art (music, theatre, dance, visual art) and literature as critical or instigative responses to issues of justice. Through analysis of existing artifacts, live performance, and creative practice, students engage with artistic processes to deepen understanding, foster empathy, and inspire social reflection and solidarity.', '["ENGL2A","ENGL12A","PHIL12A","ARTH140","ARTH143","ARTH144","ARTH145","ASCI30","CHST109","COMM131D","COMM132","COMM137","CLAS180","CLAS188","ENGL54","ENGL65","ENGL116","ENGL117","ENGL118","ENGL122","ENGL122AW","ENGL129","ENGL150EL","ENGL151A","ENGL151B","ENGL151C","ENGL162","ENGL175EL","ENGL176","ETHN65","ETHN132","ETHN136","ETHN151","ETHN164","GNSX47","GNSX115","GNSX134","GNSX134AW","GNSX139","GNSX156","GNSX183","HIST71","HIST171","FREN175","MUSC21","MUSC119","MUSC130","MUSC131","MUSC132","MUSC133","MUSC134","MUSC136","MUSC139","MUSC156","MUSC189","MUSC196","RSOC136","SCTR39","TESP46","TESP46H","TESP129","SOCI153","DANC59","DANC62","DANC159","DANC162","DANC189","THTR27","THTR44","THTR65","THTR66","THTR116","THTR117","THTR118","THTR119","THTR151","THTR161","THTR167","THTR181A"]', 'https://www.scu.edu/provost/core/integrations/pathways/pathway-listings--courses/justice--the-arts/'),
('Politics & Religion', 'This Pathway considers the relation of politics and religion in global perspective from early times to the present. Courses will invite students to explore themes of universal significance related to topics such as social, governmental, and religious systems; economics; the arts; literature; gender; race; science; the environment; and globalism.', '["ANTH12A","ARAB12A","ARTH12A","HIST12A","ENGL2A","ENGL12A","ANTH188","ARTH167","CLAS69","CLAS114","ENGL150","ENGL150EL","ETHN12","GNSX153","HIST22","HIST97","HIST107","HIST114","HIST117","HIST120","HIST126","HIST145","HIST164S","HIST166","ARAB137","POLI30","POLI139","POLI142","RSOC33","RSOC91","RSOC136","RSOC148","RSOC148R","RSOC188","RSOC190","RSOC191","SCTR65","SCTR130","SCTR157","SCTR158R","TESP43","TESP64","TESP108","TESP142","TESP158","TESP163","SOCI143"]', 'https://www.scu.edu/provost/core/integrations/pathways/pathway-listings--courses/politics--religion/'),
('Values in Science & Technology', 'This pathway invites students to critically examine the practice of science and the social dimensions of technology, exploring how social values influence scientific and technological forces in society. It includes required lower- and upper-division courses from natural sciences and engineering, as well as social sciences and humanities courses, and is open to all majors.', '["ARTH12A","ENGL2A","ENGL2AH","ENVS2A","ACTG134","ANTH1","ANTH2","ANTH4","ANTH5","ANTH130","ANTH132","ANTH133","ANTH135","ANTH136","ANTH137","ANTH140","ANTH145","ANTH147","ANTH197","ARTH140","ARTS36","BIOL1C","BIOL4","BIOL18","BIOL23","BIOL109","BIOL117","BIOL135","BIOL142","BIOL144","BIOL150","BIOL153","BIOL159","BIOL171","CENG115","CENG115L","CENG119","CENG140","CENG140L","CENG143","CENG143L","CENG144","CENG144L","CENG161","CENG219","CENG261","CHEM1","CHEM5","CHEM11","CHEM11H","CHEM14","CHEM183","CHST75","CLAS107","CLAS171","CLAS173","COEN150","COMM12","COMM106A","COMM113","COMM120A","COMM149B","COMM155","COMM156A","COMM185A","ECON111","ENGL25","ENGL108","ENGL109","ENGL110","ENGR60","ENGR90","ENGR110","ENGR160","ENGR161","ENVS2","ENVS10","ENVS20","ENVS21","ENVS22","ENVS23","ENVS80","ENVS84","ENVS120","ENVS122","ENVS135","ENVS136","ENVS137","ENVS144","ENVS145","ENVS146","ENVS147","ENVS152","ENVS153","ENVS158","ENVS185","ETHN156","ELSJ135","GNSX33","GNSX113","GNSX116","GNSX140","GNSX150","GNSX181","HIST24","HIST79","HIST179","HIST85","HIST86B","HIST123","HIST124","HIST125","HIST184","SIS471900T","CSCI3","CSCI10","CSCI10B","MECH121","MECH144","MECH144L","MGMT40","MGMT41","MGMT42","MGMT176","MGMT177","MUSC119","NEUR1","OMIS34","PHIL22","PHIL22H","PHIL27H","PHIL29","PHIL40","PHIL83","PHIL153","PHYS5","PHYS8","PHYS32","PHYS111","POLI157","PSYC50","PSYC53","PSYC53L","PSYC120","PSYC130","PSYC131","PSYC182","PHSC1","PHSC28","PHSC100","PHSC120","PHSC172","RSOC99","SCTR35","SCTR35H","SCTR170","SCTR170R","TESP64","TESP72","TESP83","TESP84","TESP86","TESP139","TESP141","